 Blockchain What is Blockchain? Definition Blockchain is a technology used to process any transaction of value using a decentralized (P2P to be specific) network of computers spread across the world.
Characterstics:  Works by a P2P network model. A transaction is called to any procedure involing debit, credit and exchange of any entity of value, hence not limited to only financial transactions.
